{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AyfF1EiXzFxfdijvSCDZdT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c9ab6b7-0c16-4e70-83e5-b7bf9f70a21f","uuid":"f63b8067-328b-44f3-bcfe-d33313775cec"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LdSujyETEAsA7gSqXYdURT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist document, not malicious.\n\nFollowing the view-contract-enforcer checklist for `entity_summary`:\n\n**1. Input validation at view boundary**\n- Parse POST body through `EntitySummaryRequest` before any business logic; reject with 400 on schema errors.\n\n**2. Explicit authorization**\n- Enforce authentication + object-level permission on the `<int:pk>` entity at the top of the view, before calling the service.\n\n**3. Service handoff**\n- View delegates to `build_entity_summary(pk, validated_request, user)`; no ORM writes or domain logic inside the view.\n\n**4. Stable response contract**\n- Serialize the service result through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it as the JSON body with an explicit status code.\n\n**5. Route + tests**\n- Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")`.\n- Add `test_entity_summary` hitting `/api/entities/1/summary/` via POST, covering: success (200 + response schema shape), validation failure (400), and access denial (401/403).\n\n**Guardrails honored**\n- No domain writes in the view — only validate, authorize, call `build_entity_summary`, serialize.\n- No ad hoc `request.data` access outside `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Tests cover both success and access/validation paths.\n\nNo files were created or modified — this run only requires applying the control checklist, per the project instructions."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":693,"cache_read_input_tokens":21716,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":693,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c9ab6b7-0c16-4e70-83e5-b7bf9f70a21f","uuid":"d3ad757d-54ff-4598-b657-b7709dad3b46"}
